# Image Rules

Always run content images through the Sharp optimization pipeline using `{% getUrl %}`. Never use a plain `src="/assets/images/..."` path for content images.

## Required pattern

Every content image must use a `<picture>` element with avif, webp, and fallback sources at appropriate sizes for mobile, tablet, and desktop:

```html
<picture class="cs-picture">
    <source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="{% getUrl "/assets/images/your-image.jpg" | resize({ width: 600, height: 400 }) | avif %}" type="image/avif">
    <source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="{% getUrl "/assets/images/your-image.jpg" | resize({ width: 600, height: 400 }) | webp %}" type="image/webp">
    <source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="{% getUrl "/assets/images/your-image.jpg" | resize({ width: 600, height: 400 }) | jpeg %}" type="image/jpeg">
    <source media="(min-width: 601px)" srcset="{% getUrl "/assets/images/your-image.jpg" | resize({ width: 1200, height: 800 }) | avif %}" type="image/avif">
    <source media="(min-width: 601px)" srcset="{% getUrl "/assets/images/your-image.jpg" | resize({ width: 1200, height: 800 }) | webp %}" type="image/webp">
    <source media="(min-width: 601px)" srcset="{% getUrl "/assets/images/your-image.jpg" | resize({ width: 1200, height: 800 }) | jpeg %}" type="image/jpeg">
    <img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="{% getUrl "/assets/images/your-image.jpg" | resize({ width: 1200, height: 800 }) | jpeg %}" alt="descriptive alt text" width="1200" height="800">
</picture>
```

Use `| png` instead of `| jpeg` for images with transparency (PNGs with no background).

Use `loading="eager"` instead of `loading="lazy"` for above-the-fold hero images.

## Exceptions

SVGs and icons do not need the pipeline — use plain `src` paths for those.
